| image            = Rom\u00e9o Elvis File7 (1).jpg\n| image_upright    = 1.2\n| caption          = Rom\u00e9o Elvis at the 20th anniversary of File7 in [[Magny-le-Hongre]], France, in 2017.\n| birth_name       = Rom\u00e9o Johnny Elvis Kiki van Laeken\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1992|12|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[Uccle]], Belgium\n| genre            = [[Hip-Hop]],[[Alternative Hip-Hop]]\n| instrument       = Voice, guitar, piano\n| years_active     = 2012\u2013present\n| associated_acts  = Le Motel [[Lomepal]]|Relatives\n| label            = Daring Music, L'\u0152il \u00c9coute Laboratoire, back in the dayz\n| website          = {{URL|romeoelvis.com/}}\n| Relatives        = Ang\u00e9le\n}}\n\n'''Rom\u00e9o Johnny Elvis Kiki van Laeken''', better known by his stage name '''Rom\u00e9o Elvis'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.letemps.ch/culture/romeo-elvis-rap-cest-nouveau-rock|title=Romeo Elvis rap c'est nouveau rock|website=Letemps.ch|date=9 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.huffingtonpost.fr/2018/03/03/romeo-elvis-nous-explique-la-difference-entre-le-rap-belge-le-rap-francais-et-nos-frites_a_23375691/|title=Romeo Elvis nous explique la difference entre le rap belge, le rap francais, et nos frites|website=HuffPost|date=3 March 2018|access-date=4 March 2018}}</ref> ({{IPA-fr|\u0281\u0254meo elvis}}), is a Belgian rapper and [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] artist. \n\nHis career began with the release of two [[Extended play|EPs]] in 2013 and 2014, titled ''Bruxelles c'est devenu la jungle'' and ''Famille nombreuse''. In 2016, his album EP ''Morale'' was released. In 2017 and 2018, two more albums were released: ''Morale 2'' and his reissue ''Morale 2 luxe'' (released from his collaboration with producer Le Motel). He has close connections with the Belgian group L'Or du Commun, the duo Caballero & JeanJass, and French rapper [[Lomepal]].\n\n== Biography ==\nRom\u00e9o Elvis was born on December 13, 1992 in [[Uccle]], [[Belgium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.konbini.com/fr/entertainment-2/frenchmen-6-romeo-elvis/|title=FRENCHMEN No. 6 : Rom\u00e9o Johnny Elvis Kiki Van Laeken, aka Rom\u00e9o Elvis|first=Rachid|last=Majdoub|date=9 April 2017|website=Konbini.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> Interested in music since his youth,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/culture-loisirs/musique/rap-romeo-elvis-roi-des-belges-a-la-conquete-de-la-france-11-02-2018-7552542.php|title=Rap : Rom\u00e9o Elvis, roi des Belges \u00e0 la conqu\u00eate de la France|first=Emmanuel|last=Marolle|date=11 February 2018|website=Le Parisien|accessdate=27 December 2018}}</ref> he developed a style distinct from that of his father, the singer [[Marka (singer)|Marka]], his mother, the comedian Laurence Bibot, and his younger sister, the singer and pianist [[Ang\u00e8le (singer)|Ang\u00e8le]]. Rom\u00e9o Elvis was raised in [[Linkebeek]], in the southern suburbs of [[Brussels]],<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|title=Rom\u00e9o Elvis, MC baryton|url=http://www.lalibre.be/culture/musique/romeo-elvis-mc-baryton-57f38b83cd70e9985fe9a675|agency=[[La Libre Belgique]]|date=6 October 2016|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> and later relocated to [[Forest, Belgium|Forest]].\n\nAfter college, he continued his secondary studies at Saint-Luc Tournai Institute where he learned to paint and draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clique.tv/qui-es-tu-romeo-elvis-le-belge-qui-simpose-dans-le-rap-francais/|title=QUI ES-TU : Rom\u00e9o Elvis, le Belge qui s'impose dans le rap fran\u00e7ais|date=15 February 2017|website=Clique.tc|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> It was during this time that Elvis began rapping with his friends. His artistic training continued at ESA 75, in Brussels, where he studied photo-journalism. While continuing to practice rap, he became close to members of L'Or du Commun.\n\nWhile his first [[Extended play|EPs]] were being released, Rom\u00e9o Elvis was working as a cashier at the supermarket chain [[Carrefour]]. Despite his success, he was not able to earn enough money from rapping alone. Shortly before the release of the album ''Bruxelles arrive'', he quit his job and devoted himself solely to music.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|title=Rom\u00e9o Elvis : \"Bruxelles est arriv\u00e9e\" L'Interview Nova serr\u00e9s dans une caisse|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rlpysmNzV2A|via=YouTube|date=7 April 2017|access-date=21 April 2017}}</ref> His newest EP, ''Morale 2luxe'', was released on February 15, 2018. ''Morale 2luxe'' is a remake of his album, ''Morale 2'', released in March 2017.\n\nElvis suffers from [[tinnitus]], common among musicians. He has made references to this condition in many of his titles, such as ''L'oreille sifflante'' and ''Ma t\u00eate.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/Romeo-elvis-ma-tete-lyrics|title=Rom\u00e9o Elvis \u2013 Ma t\u00eate|website=Genius.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> In an interview with [[Radio Nova (France)|Radio Nova]], he explained that if he could earn a substantial income from rapping he would donate some of it to fight the disease. {{Cn|date=February 2020}}\n\n== Musical style and influence ==\nThe musical style of Rom\u00e9o Elvis has evolved with the progression of his projects. While developing old-school instrumentals and a flow with similar ambiance to his first two EPs, his collaboration with the producer Le Motel on ''Morale'' and ''Morale 2'' profoundly changed his style. He currently allows himself to make more refrains and add electronic instrumentals, and in accord with the jazz of Le Motel, giving them a more current tone.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.surlmag.fr/romeo-elvis-interview-morale-2017# |title=Notre g\u00e9n\u00e9ration est plus inqui\u00e8te que la pr\u00e9c\u00e9dente |access-date=1 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713042945/http://www.surlmag.fr/romeo-elvis-interview-morale-2017/# |archive-date=13 July 2018 |url-status= |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n<span>Elvis' influences are numerous</span>: the Belgian group L'or du Commun with which he made his rapping debut is one of his main ones. Their style can also be recognized in his first two projects with group members. He also frequently mentions the rapper Caballero as someone who greatly inspired him; they met while ''Bruxelles arrive'' was being recorded. Concerning French rap, Elvis considers the rapper Alpha Wann of the group [[1995 (band)|1995]] as \"the rap master playing for me in terms of placement and in terms of how to say things in a very meaningful way\". [[Fuzati]], leader of Klub des Loosers, strongly influences the rapper. Primarily in his somber aspect, but also in the manner that the rapper holds plenty of derision towards life. He also references the masked rapper in many of his titles, like in ''Dr\u00f4le de d\u00e9cision.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/Romeo-elvis-drole-de-decision-lyrics|title=Rom\u00e9o Elvis \u2013 Dr\u00f4le de d\u00e9cision|website=Genius.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> Elvis is also a fan of the French artist [[Philippe Katerine]].\n\n== Concerts and tours ==\nWhile he began performing at concerts while growing closer to L'Or du Commun, it was during the release of ''Morale,'' in 2015, that Rom\u00e9o Elvis and Le Motel began touring, with 19 performances across Belgium, France, and Luxembourg. The release of ''Morale 2 ''also marked the beginning of another, bigger tour with 29 performances and concerts in several large festivals such as [[Dour Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dourfestival.eu/fr/program/lineup/overview/|title=Line Up \u2013 Dour Festival 2018 \u2013 11+12+13+14+15 July|website=Dourfestival.eu|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> Rock en Seine,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockenseine.com/programmation/#!programmation=artist$romeo-elvis-x-le-motel/101|title=Programmation \u2013 Rock en Seine \u2013 Festival \u2013 Paris|website=Rockenseine.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> le [[Printemps de Bourges]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.printemps-bourges.com/fr/programme/programme.html?jour=2017-04-20|title=Le Printemps de Bourges|first=Boris|last=Vedel|website=Printemps-bourges.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> and Garorock.\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center; width:10px;\"|Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center; width:220px;\"|Album\n!  style=\"text-align:center; width:20px;\" colspan=4|Peak positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center; width:70px;\"|Certification\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Ultratop|BEL<br />(Fl)]]<br /><ref name=\"bel-fl\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Rom%E9o+Elvis |title=Rom\u00e9o Elvis discography |website=ultratop.be/nl |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Ultratop|BEL<br />(Wa)]]<br /><ref name=\"bel-wa\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/fr/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Rom%E9o+Elvis |title=Rom\u00e9o Elvis discography |website=ultratop.be/fr |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[SNEP|FR]]<br /><ref name=\"fr\">{{cite web|url=https://www.lescharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Rom%E9o+Elvis |title=Rom\u00e9o Elvis discography |website=lescharts.com |accessdate=2 October 2018}}\n*\"J'ai vu\": {{Cite web|url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-singles-megafusion/?ye=2018&we=8|title=Le top de la semaine : Top Singles Megafusion|website=snepmusique.com|access-date=21 December 2018}}\n*\"1000\u00b0C\": {{Cite web|url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-singles-megafusion/?ye=2018&we=50|title=Le top de la semaine : Top Singles Megafusion|website=snepmusique.com|access-date=21 December 2018}}\n*\"Tout oublier\": {{Cite web|url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-singles-megafusion/?ye=2019&we=1|title=Le top de la semaine : Top Singles Megafusion|website=snepmu